The Zion Christian Church gathering over the Easter weekend in Moria attracts millions of people. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Zion Christian Church (ZCC) is heeding President Cyril Ramaphosa's call for no gatherings of over 100 people due to the coronavirus pandemic. The church cancelled its annual Moria pilgrimage which was set to take place over the Easter weekend. It says it made the decision last week, after meeting Health Minister Zweli Mkhize. READ: What should you do if you think you have COVID-19? The ZCC gathering over the Easter weekend in Moria attracts millions of people. "The leader took the decision on Friday after the church leadership was briefed by national government delegation by Health Minister Dr Zweli Mkhize. "We are definitely going to comply to the figure quoted by our president. "Will make sure that the church that the church leadership in each and every district or branch conforms to the right number where people should be together." READ: How does the coronavirus test work? 4 questions answered Meanwhile, the number of confirmed cases of coronavirus has risen to 85 with 23 new cases that have been reported. Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. South Africans are being asked to clean their hands with soap and water to deal with the coronavirus. But is that even possible when some communities don't even have proper running water? There have been calls for water tankers to be provided for areas without infrastructure. Courtesy #DStv403